## ----compas, fig.cap = "Empirical per-race coverage from marginal APS and Mondrian APS on COMPAS two-year recidivism, target 0.90. Data: ProPublica COMPAS dataset (6167 defendants after standard ProPublica screening). Caucasian and African-American subgroups shown. Dashed line at 0.90 marks target coverage. Marginal APS over-covers both groups by including both outcome classes in the prediction set frequently enough to hit 100 per cent empirically. Mondrian APS computes a separate calibration quantile per group and tracks the 0.90 target more tightly on each.", fig.alt = "A grouped bar chart with two groups on the horizontal axis (Caucasian and African-American) and two bars per group (marginal APS and Mondrian APS). A horizontal dashed line at 0.90 marks target coverage. The marginal APS bars reach 1.00 in both groups, over-covering. The Mondrian APS bars sit close to the dashed line at 0.90 in both groups, showing tight tracking of the target within each subgroup."----
